.TH "set_rxq_intr_params" 9 "set_rxq_intr_params" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
set_rxq_intr_params \- set a queue's interrupt holdoff parameters
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" set_rxq_intr_params
.BI "(struct adapter *adapter "  ","
.BI "struct sge_rspq *rspq "  ","
.BI "unsigned int us "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cnt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adapter" 12
the adapter
.IP "rspq" 12
the RX response queue
.IP "us" 12
the hold-off time in us, or 0 to disable timer
.IP "cnt" 12
the hold-off packet count, or 0 to disable counter

Sets an RX response queue's interrupt hold-off time and packet count.
At least one of the two needs to be enabled for the queue to generate
interrupts.
